<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="335" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,835,1257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1087,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="335">Remarks</emphasis>
. Following 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwank, P." box="[443,645,1087,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="335" pagination="1 - 262" refId="ref13700" refString="Schwank, P. (1990) Gastrotricha. In: Braur, A., Schwoerbel, J. &amp; Zwick, P. (Eds.), Susswasser Fauna von Mitteleuropa. Band 3. Heft 1. 2. Gastrotricha und Nemertini. Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart and Jenai, pp. i - xvi + 1 - 262." type="book chapter" year="1990">Schwank’s (1990)</bibRefCitation>
classification, 
<bibRefCitation author="Naidu, K. V. &amp; Rao, G. C." box="[812,1041,1087,1114]" pageId="3" pageNumber="335" pagination="169" refId="ref12873" refString="Naidu, K. V. &amp; Rao, G. C. (2004) Gastrotricha. In: Fauna of India and the adjacent countries. Zoological Survey of India, Kol- kata, pp. 169." type="book chapter" year="2004">Naidu &amp; Rao (2004)</bibRefCitation>
in their review reported the species as belonging to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Schwank, 1990" authorityName="Schwank" authorityYear="1990" box="[491,657,1123,1149]" class="Not" family="Chaetonotidae" genus="Euchaetonotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="3" pageNumber="335" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[491,657,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="335">Euchaetonotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is invalid (
<bibRefCitation author="Kisielewski, J." box="[872,1075,1123,1149]" pageId="3" pageNumber="335" pagination="145 - 151" refId="ref12395" refString="Kisielewski, J. (1997) On the subgeneric division of the genus Chaetonotus Ehrenberg (Gastrotricha). Annales Zoologici, 46, 145 - 151." type="journal article" year="1997">Kisielewski 1997</bibRefCitation>
). The specimens found in 
<collectingCountry box="[1379,1437,1123,1149]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="335">India</collectingCountry>
seems to fit rather well the description of the species from e.g., Europe, with the possible exception of the ventral side for which details have not been reported or appear in contrast with what it is known for the taxon (see e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Sharma, B. K." box="[151,300,1231,1257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="335" pagination="265 - 267" refId="ref13765" refString="Sharma, B. K. (1980) Taxonomic notes on some freshwater Gastrotricha from West Bengal, India. Hydrobiologia, 70, 265 - 267. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00016769" type="journal article" year="1980">Sharma 1980</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis box="[307,330,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="335">vs</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schwank, P." box="[337,507,1231,1257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="335" pagination="1 - 262" refId="ref13700" refString="Schwank, P. (1990) Gastrotricha. In: Braur, A., Schwoerbel, J. &amp; Zwick, P. (Eds.), Susswasser Fauna von Mitteleuropa. Band 3. Heft 1. 2. Gastrotricha und Nemertini. Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart and Jenai, pp. i - xvi + 1 - 262." type="book chapter" year="1990">Schwank 1990</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
